race.comment: DARN HOT MISS (2) impressed last time out at the second run of the campaign and finished 5 lengths from the winner in third over 1600m at Seymour. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. DREAMSTONE (7) lines up on the back of a 3.5 lengths fifth over 2000m at Wangaratta. Credentials hard to knock. UNDER THE HAT (13) finished second last time over 1400m at Albury, beaten 4.5 lengths. Taking on a better field but she is up to the task. POETS ARTISTRY (3) is a last-start winner three-and-a-half weeks ago, scoring by half a length over 1400m at Echuca. Has solid credentials. CONTROVERSIAL MISS (1) has been racing consistently this prep and the combination of weight relief and a good barrier should ensure she gets her chance.
